1. Install the heroku CLI
```bash
brew tap heroku/brew && brew install heroku
```

2. Register the heroku apps as a git remote

```bash
heroku git:remote -a ibappx-tasktracker-backend
git remote rename heroku backend
heroku git:remote -a ibappx-tasktracker-webapp
git remote rename heroku webapp
```

3. Register the buildpack
```bash
heroku buildpacks:add -a ibappx-tasktracker-webapp heroku-community/multi-procfile
heroku buildpacks:add -a ibappx-tasktracker-backend heroku-community/multi-procfile
heroku config:set -a ibappx-tasktracker-webapp PROCFILE=react-task-tracker/Procfile
$ heroku config:set -a ibappx-tasktracker-backend PROCFILE=task-tracker-backend/Procfile
```

4. Commit any code (it must be commited to deploy) and push changes:

```bash
git push heroku ${BRANCH_NAME}:main
```